{"session_id":"svc-1779913469417283294","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-27T20:24:30.5751087Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"haiku","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"haiku","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-52d1c006-20260527T202343-6e709e45","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Do not mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; do not use parallel tool calls for `git add`, `git commit`, or other staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 still allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add`, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Long-running matrix/benchmark beads\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For expensive commands (benchmarks, load tests, validation \u0026gt; 60s per variant):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Write a matrix plan before launching expensive commands: list required configs, output paths, completion criteria.\u0026#xA;- Do not re-run the same long-running command unless: (1) the command fingerprint changed (args/env/config), AND (2) you document why prior output is invalid and what changed.\u0026#xA;- If a long-running command times out or is incomplete, exit with `status: open` + retryable `reason` in `no_changes_rationale.txt`. Do not silently retry; let the orchestrator decide.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-52d1c006\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eLock readiness_checks JSON schema in a shared location with a CI drift gate\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;Schema drift between the readiness-check producer (prompt/harness) and the pre_claim_intake consumer caused the verdict=bool failure that idled the entire fizeau queue (Fizeau 2026-05-18). One side emitted verdict as bool, the other parsed it as string. Without a single source of truth referenced by both sides and a CI gate, the same class of silent drift recurs.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;Producer and consumer historically encoded the readiness_checks contract independently; there was no shared schema enforced across both. The consumer decoder lives in cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_hook.go and the verdict field is decoded at cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_hook.go:77-125; nothing pins the producer to the same contract.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX (parent proposed-fix B)\u0026#xA;Define the readiness_checks JSON schema in a shared location at cli/internal/agent/schema/readiness-checks.schema.json (readiness_checks as a JSON array; each item has reason, verdict as oneOf boolean|string|null, evidence, checkable_before_attempt). Reference it from the consumer via a constant readinessChecksSchemaPath at cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_hook.go:21 and from the producer prompt. Add a test that validates representative payloads (verdict bool, string, and null) against the schema and fails on drift between the code contract and the schema file.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DEPENDS ON\u0026#xA;The pre-claim intake decoder child (verdict coercion to a canonical readinessVerdict type) must land first, because the schema\u0026#39;s canonical verdict forms are defined there.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Decoder coercion implementation (sibling decoder child; this is its dependency).\u0026#xA;- Warn-fingerprint escalation (sibling child).\u0026#xA;- claim-rate operator signal (sibling child).\u0026#xA;- README documentation (sibling child).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CROSS-REF\u0026#xA;Governing artifact: AR-2026-05-17 follow-up beads. Adjacent silent-failure bugs: ddx-57c40485, ddx-8f2e0ebf.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. readiness_checks JSON schema is defined at cli/internal/agent/schema/readiness-checks.schema.json with verdict as oneOf boolean|string|null, and is the single source of truth both producer and consumer reference; verified by TestReadinessChecksSchema in cli/internal/agent/readiness_schema_test.go.\u0026#xA;2. The consumer decoder references the shared schema path constant (readinessChecksSchemaPath, cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_hook.go:21) and drift between the code contract and the schema fails TestReadinessChecksSchema.\u0026#xA;3. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... green.\u0026#xA;4. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:pre-claim, area:execute-bead, kind:reliability, observability, triage:no-changes-unjustified\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-f9ddaa68\" base-rev=\"d54e4a5a88fbb0bc60583a4f35c06b72779d807b\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260527T202343-6e709e45\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-52d1c006-20260527T202343-6e709e45/.ddx/executions/20260527T202343-6e709e45/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-52d1c006-20260527T202343-6e709e45/.ddx/executions/20260527T202343-6e709e45/embedded/git-bin:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/bun/1.3.11/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/node/22.21.1/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/erik/.local/share/coursier/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-fuzzy/bin:/home/erik/go/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/scripts:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/scripts:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/Coursier/bin:/home/erik/.lmstudio/bin:/home/erik/.cache/lm-